cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.DS 

This paper deals with scheduling algorithms for multiple access in a network, which involves communication and information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), and system design (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed algorithms in terms of complexity and convergence, which falls under the category of machine learning and optimization (cs.MA). Finally, the paper provides simulation results to support the proposed methods, which involves data analysis and statistics (cs.DS).
